# Approved artifacts. One line per category. Paths are relative to prototype/.
# Edit when an artifact's approval state changes; the launcher and skills read
# this file to know which versions are the source of truth.
#
# Categories used by the toolchain:
#   prd:       the approved PRD (e.g., prd/site-prd.md)
#   prototype: the approved interactive prototype (e.g., hi-fi/cool-minimal-v1.html)
#   theme:     the approved theme tokens (typically tokens.css)
#
# Skills write into this file when the user signs off:
#   prd-crit          → writes/updates `prd:` when PRD is marked Ready
#   design-prototypes → writes/updates `prototype:` when user picks "the one"
#   design-themes     → writes/updates `theme:` when a theme is committed
#   design-components → reads `prototype:` to know what to extract from
#
# Add categories ad-hoc as needed; tools that don't recognize a key just ignore it.
